E.g. cognitive interviewing - question testing. Like a usability test but you can use a script and interviewer interacts with the list of questions. (E.g. go to qu 27). Can probe and ask people what they think.

Or make a prototype (a minimalist one) and let user interact with the thing. See Andrew D’s markup (). A paper doc.
Usually a paper/electronic hybrid

Start your paper form design ahead of the digital equivalent. It’s easy to rapidly prototype paper forms and to make them live ahead of your digital service.

Focus on the words and questions, the structure and flow at this stage.


